  • Class
    Description
    AirConditioningEventI
    The interface AirConditioningEventI enforces a common type for all AirConditioning simulation events.
    Cool
    The class Cool defines the simulation event of the AirConditioning starting to cool.
    DoNotCool
    The class DoNotCool defines the simulation event of the AirConditioning stopping to cool.
    SetPowerAirConditioning
    The class SetPowerAirConditioning defines the simulation event of the AirConditioning power being set to some level (in watts).
    SetPowerAirConditioning.PowerValue
    The class PowerValue represent a power value to be passed as an EventInformationI when creating a SetPowerAirConditioning event.
    SwitchOffAirConditioning
    The class SwitchOffAirConditioning defines the simulation event of the AirConditioning being switched off.
    SwitchOnAirConditioning
    The class SwitchOnAirConditioning defines the simulation event of the AirConditioning being switched on.
